    {
      "id": "p004",
      "index": 4,
      "source": "CPUs are now featuring more in the networking stack. While previous SmartNICs and Data Processing Units (DPUs) added some ARM cores to the Ethernet controllers to perform in-network offloads and accelerations, NVIDIA takes this to the next level with their latest DPU. They are now co-packaging an entire Grace CPU alongside a ConnectX-9 chip for the Bluefield-4 DPU, used in each Rubin compute tray for the frontend NIC as well as putting four BF4s in their Context Memory Storage Platform for KV-Cache offload to high-speed NAND.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0303",
      "parent_block_index": 303,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "CPUs are now featuring more in the networking stack. While previous SmartNICs and Data Processing Units (DPUs) added some ARM cores to the Ethernet controllers to perform in-network offloads and accelerations, NVIDIA takes this to the next level with their latest DPU. They are now co-packaging an entire Grace CPU alongside a ConnectX-9 chip for the Bluefield-4 DPU, used in each Rubin compute tray for the frontend NIC as well as putting four BF4s in their Context Memory Storage Platform for KV-Cache offload to high-speed NAND.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "CPUs are now featuring more in the networking stack. While previous SmartNICs and Data Processing Units (DPUs) added some ARM cores to the Ethernet controllers to perform in-network offloads and accelerations, NVIDIA takes this to the next level with their latest DPU. They are now co-packaging an entire Grace CPU alongside a ConnectX-9 chip for the Bluefield-4 DPU, used in each Rubin compute tray for the frontend NIC as well as putting four BF4s in their Context Memory Storage Platform for KV-Cache offload to high-speed NAND.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [],
      "segment_start": 0,
      "segment_end": 531,
      "expected_tokens": [],
      "format_recovery_status": "not_applicable",
      "format_errors": [],
      "is_heading": false,
      "heading_level": null,
      "heading_chain": [],
      "is_metadata": false,
      "metadata_type": null,
      "translations": {
        "pro": {
          "text": "CPU 在网络栈中的比重日益增加。此前的智能网卡（SmartNIC）和数据处理器（DPU）仅在以太网控制器中加入少量 ARM 内核，用于执行网络内卸载与加速。如今，英伟达凭借最新款 DPU 将这一设计推向了新高度。在 Bluefield-4 DPU 中，英伟达直接将一整颗 Grace CPU 与 ConnectX-9 芯片进行共封装。每个 Rubin 计算托盘均将该 DPU 用作前端网卡；此外，英伟达还在其上下文内存存储平台中配置了 4 颗 BF4，专门用于将 KV-Cache 卸载至高速 NAND 闪存。",
          "model": "pro",
          "created_at": "2026-04-08T16:51:12.533631",
          "tokenized_text": null,
          "format_issues": []
        }
      },
      "confirmed": null,
